Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.61,0:00:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers, do you recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.58,0:00:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see this finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.04,0:00:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it? Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.75,0:00:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.30,0:00:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.68,0:00:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.26,0:00:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.10,0:00:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming? What's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.77,0:00:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.11,0:00:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.99,0:00:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.21,0:02:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.50,0:02:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're able to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.93,0:02:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the four murders of middle-aged\Ncouples in the past two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.18,0:02:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you were seen near the scene\Nof three of them, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.48,0:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it, Adolph Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.61,0:02:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that\Nyou are a lock picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.99,0:02:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your job is just to open locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Slitting throats in a single stroke\Nis not something you could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.46,0:03:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That means there were other\Nperpetrators in addition to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.51,0:03:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that there would have to be\Nat least three people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.34,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to open a strong lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and murder a middle-aged couple\Nwithout resistance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.52,0:03:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost finished\Nmaking a list of men who use knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.31,0:03:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a matter of time\Nbefore we pinpoint your colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.99,0:03:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you talk, or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.37,0:03:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not what\NI really want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.79,0:03:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why four couples\Nfrom across Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And why only kill\Nmiddle-aged ones without children?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.05,0:03:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Money and items were stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.26,0:03:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but the amounts were too small
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.93,0:04:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to split three ways to justify murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?\NWant to make a plea bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.23,0:04:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make a statement,\Nyou can escape prosecution...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.29,0:04:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers. that's enough.\NThat's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to ask you to\Nend this questioning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.30,0:04:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.59,0:04:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order from\Nhis attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.\NI'll come again another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.97,0:04:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will place a guard\Nto watch him closely
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he isn't poisoned\Nor that he doesn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.36,0:04:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:05:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of trouble\Nseems to happen around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.53,0:05:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.91,0:05:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You, where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing things without permission\Nis going to get me in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.81,0:05:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Even patients need recreation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going out into the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worried,\Ndo you want to come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a warm and pleasant day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can talk, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,On days like this,\Nit makes you glad you're alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.51,0:06:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I need days like this,\Nor else it becomes unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I see people in\Nlife and death situations every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's easier for doctors to\Nfocus on fame and research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to gain a reputation\Nand do my own research...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that succeeding in surgery\Nwas a way to fortify my status...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But after performing surgery\Non a certain boy, I changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the elder of fraternal twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd been shot in the head.\NBecause I saved him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to return to being a real doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.63,0:06:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of people's lives\Nare all the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.47,0:06:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor's work\Nis to save those lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.69,0:06:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.78,0:07:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start over.\NIt's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.96,0:07:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are close in age,\Nbut you're like my old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.92,0:07:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.47,0:07:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like you're my parent...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly have a big kid, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.68,0:07:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little,\NI wanted a mechanical clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.48,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould stroll out on the hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.28,0:07:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, I would press my face against\Nthe show window of the watch store...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.37,0:07:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My first break in was that store...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.54,0:08:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They caught me right away\Nand I didn't get the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But, after that,\Nbreak ins became my job...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, it was only because\NI wanted that clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wanted the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.65,0:08:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the police everything\Nand start over from scratch...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.12,0:08:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My associates, all of them...\NThey were all killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who killed them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.25,0:08:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you called "the monster"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.85,0:08:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Make this one yours, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot of trouble\Nto set this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.36,0:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the daughter of a member of\Nthe state parliament, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She is beautiful and intelligent.\NShe's really something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.07,0:09:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to meet her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But... I guess...\NI should do as you say and settle down...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.83,0:09:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You should!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.62,0:09:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone with your prestige\Nto not have a wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.47,0:09:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould pop out every hour...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.85,0:09:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.27,0:09:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!\NAbout the clock in the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.40,0:09:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.98,0:09:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already time for your date! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.04,0:10:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can start over.\NIt's not too late.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.93,0:10:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Policeman on watch...\NYou're there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.23,0:10:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.69,0:10:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you call Dr. Tenma, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late, but can I visit\None of the rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.68,0:10:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:10:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I found something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.49,0:11:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.54,0:11:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.92,0:11:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the same as the last time!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.61,0:11:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Poisoned by candy! My patient's disappeared!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.32,0:11:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the same thing that happened\Nnine years ago!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.11,0:12:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.45,0:12:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't come, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the hospital,\NMr. Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.20,0:12:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.96,0:12:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't see him, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.93,0:13:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.22,0:13:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one\Nwho killed my accomplices!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.10,0:13:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be killed, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor! You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.03,0:13:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago, you saved my life,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already forgotten\Nabout those twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.39,0:13:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.53,0:14:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, those twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!\NYou'll be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.62,0:14:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.29,0:14:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers is my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Execute him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.14,0:14:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He killed my friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We were hired by him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He always called us on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.19,0:14:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A large reward was transferred into\Nour account after each job was done...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd split it between the three of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.74,0:14:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who ordered the murders\Nof the four middle-aged couples
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.33,0:14:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The police were watching me,\Nso we became a hindrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.00,0:15:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already killed Fritz, the Slayer,\Nand Big Boy Boris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.26,0:15:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before he died, Fritz said,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"We've been hired by a monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't think anything of\Nkilling people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Run! Doctor, you'll be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.98,0:15:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Run, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk too much, Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.99,0:15:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers doesn't seem to know\Nwho you are, but I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.62,0:15:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was your attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.70,0:15:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Johan Leibert,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the elder of twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the son of Michael Leibert, former\Nadvisor of Commerce in East Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.71,0:15:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who defected to West Germany in 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.34,0:15:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If we know this much about you,\Nyou can't possibly escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.68,0:15:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't add to your crimes, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.52,0:15:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan?\NI used that name before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not my real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.53,0:16:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.78,0:16:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My past must not be known...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.66,0:16:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Those four couples\Nand the Leiberts, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.79,0:16:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're different, Doctor...\NYou saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like my parent, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Parent... me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, if it weren't for you,\NI wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.01,0:16:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!\NYou mustn't kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.98,0:16:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.27,0:16:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why not?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.94,0:16:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think a human life is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.82,0:16:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to go back to being\Nwhat a doctor should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,By saving your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.41,0:16:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that\Nthe weight of each life is equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has the right to\Ntake another person's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:17:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived for many years as a doctor\Nwith that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.85,0:17:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, after that incident, I heard you\Nsoon became the Chief of Surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.98,0:17:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad that you were selected\Nas the Chief of Surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here now because the Director, the Chief of Surgery and the Chief died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.58,0:17:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really good...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be... You did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.17,0:17:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you said it yourself...\NThis is what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.55,0:17:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became conscious,\Nthat's what you said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.68,0:17:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That you hated them so much\Nyou could kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I am not wrong!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.52,0:18:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That bastard... That bastard...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's better off dead.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.95,0:18:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I did just as you wished, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.08,0:18:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor... I'm afraid, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor... Save me, Doctor...\NI don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.66,0:19:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to have died back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.12,0:19:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought me back to life, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.12,0:19:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, this rain is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate the rain. It washes away\Nall the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.42,0:19:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.31,0:20:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... That means,\Nfrom what you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1986, right after the Leiberts defected\Nfrom East Germany with their twin children,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.24,0:20:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the Leibert family was shot\Nand the parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.08,0:20:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder of the twins, the boy,\Nwas hit in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.08,0:20:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You operated on the boy\Nand saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.84,0:20:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But, surprisingly, the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.05,0:20:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,killed the director, chief of surgery\Nand head of neurosurgery
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with poisoned candy and ran away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night, he appeared\Nafter nine years
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.18,0:20:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed a state police officer,\Nonce again with poisoned candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And shot Adolph Junkers\Nright in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.90,0:21:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one who hired Junkers and two others\Nto kill the four middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Johan Leibert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.37,0:21:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.51,0:21:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.55,0:21:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you ever think that someone with Dr. Tenma's credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.73,0:21:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,would ever commit such a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He has an alibi for the time\Nthe policeman was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.27,0:21:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was no gunpowder residue\Non his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.86,0:21:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the clue to solving\Nthe murders
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.99,0:21:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the four middle-aged couples\Nis gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.20,0:21:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, shall we\Ngo after the guy, Johan Leibert?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.96,0:21:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.25,0:22:36.92,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And slowly, you come to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.46,0:22:44.34,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's all as it should be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.22,0:22:53.77,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You can only do so much
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.94,0:22:59.36,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}If you're game enough
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.78,0:23:07.16,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You could place your trust in me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:16.25,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}For the love of life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.38,0:23:21.59,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's a trade off
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.38,0:23:28.35,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We could lose it all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.35,0:23:33.27,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But we'll go down fighting
